examples.en: I adjusted the volume on the radio.
We adjusted our watches to local time.
He adjusted the hang of his coat.
She adjusted the drape of her skirt.
I adjusted the volume knob and sat down.
He adjusted the intensity of the sound.
He raised his binoculars and adjusted the focus.
The car is easier to drive since the clutch was adjusted.
She adjusted the car seat so she could reach the pedals.
If your employment status changes, your tax code will be adjusted accordingly.
The long run is a period of time sufficiently long, such that all factors of production can be fully adjusted.
